<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="397">Note:</emphasis>
Townsend (in Nasir &amp; Ali, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="397">Fl. W. Pakistani</emphasis>
71: 5. 1974) indicated 288.4 (LINN) as the 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
but this sheet lacks the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="397">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number (i.e. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“2”">&quot;2&quot;</normalizedToken>
) and is a post-1753 addition to the collection and not original material for the name. Smith (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="397">Fl Vitiensis Nova</emphasis>
2: 285. 1981) stated that the Clifford reference &quot;suggests the suitable 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
&quot;, but there are seven sheets (evidently not from a single gathering) associated with this name in the Clifford herbarium, so this is not an effective choice.
</paragraph>
